New Records: Jack Kochanowicz posted a 3.05 ERA in 44 1/3 innings over his last seven outings
Key Match Events: The game went into 13 innings before a decisive walk-off hit by Jordyn Adams
Pre-Game Insights: Kochanowicz has bounced back to go on an impressive run to put himself in a good spot heading into next season
Post-Match Reflections: Kochanowicz's impressive start was spoiled by the late collapse of the Angels, but he bounced back with a quality start in the 13th inning
Miscellaneous Highlights: Kochanowicz's sinker was again his bread and butter, throwing it 57 times and topping out at 98 mph
Others: The Angels also got a look at No. 1 prospect Caden Dana, who struggled in consecutive starts, on Sunday before shutting him down for the season
